  "description": "Large dark falcon came in harassing the gulls before they all took off.\u00a0 The back was solid gray and the underside was dark and streaky with thick streaks revealing little white (light) on the underside.\u00a0 The wings and tail were very broad.\u00a0 The legs were bluish and the face was plainer and less patterend than a Peregrine Falcon.\u00a0 Photos show all diagnostic marks.\u00a0 I was unsure of the identification in the field until doing research at home.",
